The paper discusses anomaly detection, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer security. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for semi-supervised anomaly detection, which involves both unsupervised and supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
